        "body": "<pre><code>contents.getChars(first, second, arr, 0);\nchar ch = arr[i];\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This copies a character from <code>contents<\/code> into <code>arr[0]<\/code> not <code>arr[i]<\/code>. So changing the second line to <code>char ch = arr[0];<\/code> should work. But there are easier ways to access characters from a String. See 'charAt' or 'toCharArray'.<\/p>\n",
